{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This quick start guide uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Although not strictly required, it simplifies many aspects of cross-platform distribution and provides a platform-agnostic configuration format for specifying things such as app icons and custom URL schemes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re new to Swift, we recommend starting with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"text":"Installing Swift Bundler","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Installing-Swift-Bundler"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler?tab=readme-ov-file#installation-"},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"code":"mint","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the preferred installation method on macOS and Linux as of the last update to this quick start guide."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Installing system dependencies","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Installing-system-dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each backend has different requirements. In this guide we’ll use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" which uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on macOS, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on Linux, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on Windows, and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS\/tvOS. Click through the backend relevant to your machine for detailed installation requirements. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" have no system dependencies."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Using Swift Bundler’s SwiftCrossUI template","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Using-Swift-Bundlers-SwiftCrossUI-template"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Bundler provides many built-in templates; we’ll use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftCrossUI"},{"text":" template. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftCrossUI"},{"text":" template uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DefaultBackend"},{"text":" to select the most appropriate backend at compile time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["swift bundler create HelloWorld --template SwiftCrossUI","cd HelloWorld"]},{"text":"Running your app","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Running-your-app"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Running your new app with Swift Bundler is as simple as it gets!","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["swift bundler run"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On macOS you can provide the "},{"code":"--device <device_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option to run the app on a connected iOS or tvOS device, or the "},{"code":"--simulator <simulator_name_or_id>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option to run the app in a simulator."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing","code":["# You can use any substring of the target device name. For example,","# \"iPhone\" matches any device connected with \"iPhone\" in its name.","swift bundler run --device \"iPhone\"","swift bundler run --simulator \"iPhone 15\""]},{"text":"Making a change","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Making-a-change"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sources\/HelloWorld\/HelloWorldApp.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in an editor of your choosing. Change ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Hello, World!\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Hello, Earth!\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Repeat the previous step to verify that your changes get reflected.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"All done","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"All-done"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’re good to go! If you make something cool with SwiftCrossUI let us know so we can add your project to our showcase once the SwiftCrossUI website is up and running!"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/quick-start"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating a cross-platform SwiftCrossUI app with Swift Bundler."}],"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Getting Started","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Setting-up-a-virtual-development-environment","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Examples","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Hot-reloading"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Getting-Started"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/